TITLE: Inserting JSON File into Lix
DESCRIPTION: Example of inserting a JSON file into the Lix system using the database API
SOURCE: https://github.com/opral/monorepo/blob/main/packages/lix-sdk/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const json = {
	name: "Hello World",
	version: "1.0.0",
	settings: {
		enableFeatureX: true,
		maxUsers: 10,
	},
};

// Insert the file 
const file = await lix.db
	.insertInto("file")
	.values({
		path: "/example.json",
		data: new TextEncoder().encode(JSON.stringify(json)),
	})
	.returningAll()
	.executeTakeFirstOrThrow();

console.log("JSON file inserted with ID:", file.id);
```

