TITLE: Troubleshooting incorrect locale handling with paraglideMiddleware
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating common mistake of calling getLocale() outside the paraglideMiddleware scope. The middleware establishes correct request-specific locale context, so locale functions should only be called within its scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opral/monorepo/blob/main/inlang/packages/paraglide/paraglide-js/docs/server-side-rendering.md#2025-04-21_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
app.get("*", async (request) => {
  // ‚ùå don't call `getLocale()` outside of `paraglideMiddleware`
  const locale = getLocale()

  return paraglideMiddleware(request, async ({ request, locale }) => {
    // ‚úÖ call `getLocale()` inside of `paraglideMiddleware`
    const locale = getLocale()

    // Your request handling logic here
    return Response(html(request));
  });
});
```

