TITLE: Configuring URL Patterns for Multi-Tenant i18n in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure URL patterns for multi-tenant internationalization using the compile function. It sets up different localization strategies for specific domains and a default strategy for other domains.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opral/monorepo/blob/main/inlang/packages/paraglide/paraglide-js/docs/multi-tenancy.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
await compile({
	project: "./project.inlang",
	strategy: ["url"],
	urlPatterns: [
		// 1) customer1.fr => root locale is fr, sub-locale is /en/
		{
			pattern: "https://customer1.fr/:path(.*)?",
			localized: [
				["fr", "https://customer1.fr/:path(.*)?"],
				["en", "https://customer1.fr/en/:path(.*)?"],
			],
		},
		// 2) customer2.com => root locale is en, sub-locale is /fr/
		{
			pattern: "https://customer2.com/:path(.*)?",
			localized: [
				["en", "https://customer2.com/:path(.*)?"],
				["fr", "https://customer2.com/fr/:path(.*)?"],
			],
		},
		// 3) Any other domain => path-based for en/fr
		{
			pattern: "https://:domain(.*)/:path(.*)?",
			localized: [
				["en", "https://:domain(.*)/en/:path(.*)?"],
				["fr", "https://:domain(.*)/fr/:path(.*)?"],
			],
		},
	],
});
```

