TITLE: Localized Pattern Order Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to properly order localized patterns within URL configurations, particularly for path-based localization with prefixes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opral/monorepo/blob/main/inlang/packages/paraglide/paraglide-js/docs/strategy.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// ‚ùå INCORRECT ORDER: The first pattern is too general
{
  pattern: "https://example.com/:path(.*)?",
  localized: [
    ["en", "https://example.com/:path(.*)?"]
    ["en", "https://example.com/en/blog/:id"]
  ],
}

// ‚úÖ CORRECT ORDER: Specific patterns first, then more general patterns
{
  pattern: "https://example.com/:path(.*)?",
  localized: [
    ["en", "https://example.com/en/blog/:id"],
    ["en", "https://example.com/:path(.*)?"]
  ],
}

// ‚ùå INCORRECT ORDER FOR DELOCALIZATION: Generic pattern first will cause problems
{
  pattern: "/:path(.*)?",
  localized: [
    ["en", "/:path(.*)?"]
    ["de", "/de/:path(.*)?"]
  ],
}

// ‚úÖ CORRECT ORDER: More specific patterns with prefixes should come first
{
  pattern: "/:path(.*)?",
  localized: [
    ["de", "/de/:path(.*)?"]
    ["en", "/:path(.*)?"]
  ],
}
```

